- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The integer parameter `difference` must be greater than or equal to -10000 and less than or equal to 10000.
- The integer result is the length of the longest subsequence in the integer array `arr` which is an arithmetic sequence such that the difference between adjacent elements in the subsequence equals the integer parameter `difference`.
- The length of the integer array `arr` is less than or equal to 100000.